[32m│[0m ## Thoughts                                                                  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The IDOR vulnerability is confirmed and exploited successfully. The          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m application lacks proper authorization checks when processing the profile    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m update request. The hidden `username` field in the update form is processed  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m on the server side without verifying that the authenticated user (test) has  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m permission to modify that user's profile. By changing the username parameter [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m from "test" to "admin", I was able to update the admin user's email address, [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m which triggered the flag disclosure in the response.                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The vulnerability pattern is: **No access control verification on object     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m (username) parameter** combined with **client-side hidden field trust**.     [32m│[0m
